      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just a note about a problem I hit when doing something similar. :(\n\ndigit@\u0027s pipe refactor CL created a C interface to be implemented in the QEMU glue code.\nThis one creates a C++ interface for the same reason.\n\nLiking C++, I went down the path of a C++ interface for the console refactor, but hit a snag -- it\u0027s not always safe to include C headers from C++.\nSo far, I\u0027ve seen at least two problems:\n- Some qemu headers under include/* that declare a global without \u0027extern\u0027. This works fine as long as they\u0027re only included from C files.\n- Some target specific headers use typeof. That\u0027s a strict no-no for C++.\n\nSo, if you get lucky the C++ strategy will work...",
