      "side": 1,
      "message": "To some extent.\nI think it\u0027s cleaner and easier to just let the QEMU glue provide C-interfaces that AndroidEmu can use in C++ code.\n\nThe header that declares the interface is part of AndroidEmu.\nAnd we can add one / few headers in QEMU{1,2} that merely make objects for those interfaces available, without pulling in any other QEMU headers.\n\nThis lets us cleanly separate out arbitrary QEMU C headers from C++ code.",
